ZCZC GE62
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 232300 UTC
ON TUESDAY EVENING A LARGE AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE 1036
WILL BE CENTRED IN MID-ATLANTIC WITH A LOW PRESSURE
CENTRE 991 OVER THE BALTIC. THE LOW CENTRE WILL MIGRATE
EWARDS DURING WEDNESDAY WITH PRESSURE REMAINING HIGH IN
THE ATLANTIC UNTIL THURSDAY MORNING. THROUGH THURSDAY THE
HIGH CENTRE WILL SLIP SWARDS BUT ALSO EXTEND A RIDGE
ACROSS THE UK WITH PRESSURE FALLING NEAR ICELAND.
PRESSURE MAY BUILD ACROSS THE UK AT FIRST ON FRIDAY BUT
MOV SWARDS LATER ALLOWING PRESSURE TO FALL IN THE N. ON
TUESDAY EVENING N WINDS WILL BE STRG IN THE N SEA WITH
OCCASIONAL GALES IN THE N THEN WINDS WILL GRADUALLY MOD
THROUGH WEDNESDAY ALTHOUGH PERHAPS CONTINUING STRG IN
FAIR ISLE. SIMILAR WINDS ARE FCST ON THURSDAY OCNL STRG
SW IN FAIR ISLE. ON FRIDAY STRG SW WINDS MAY RETURN TO
NERN SEA AREAS WITH OCCASIONAL GALES POSS LATER IN FAIR
ISLE AND VIKING
